---
<section class="section day-bg" id="booth">
  <div class="memory-inner">
    <div class="memory-text">
      <div class="section-label">Photo Booth</div>
      <h2>The Fam Jam Booth</h2>
      <p class="big-sub">Not just silly photos.</p>
      <p>
        This is how your family actually gets a real photo together. We bring a DSLR, flattering
        lighting, and custom print templates — so people walk away with something worth keeping,
        not just a shared album link nobody opens.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:20px; font-size:.92rem; color:rgba(18,22,42,.65); line-height:1.75;">
        The average Fam Jam event generates
        <strong style="color:#b0298a;">400+ digital images</strong> — candid moments, group shots,
        and the kind of photos you don't usually get at a party.
      </p>
      <ul class="memory-features">
        <li>Crisp 2x6 or 4x6 prints on the spot</li>
        <li>Custom theme-matched print design</li>
        <li>Onsite attendant the whole time</li>
        <li>400+ high-res digital images per event</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="font-style:italic; font-weight:600; color:#b0298a; margin-bottom:32px;">
        People actually keep these prints.
      </p>
      <div class="booth-addon-callout">
        <div class="addon-label">✦ Add-On — $200</div>
        <h4>Party Photos &amp; Social Reel</h4>
        <p>
          We'll capture photos and short video clips throughout the event — enough to cut together
          a social media reel. Not a full event photographer, just us documenting the vibe as it
          happens.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="memory-visual">
      <div class="photo-frame">
        <img
          src="/images/Photobooth-4.jpg"
          alt="Fam Jam photo booth print"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="print-strip">
        <div class="print-thumb">2×6 Print</div>
        <div class="print-thumb">4×6 Print</div>
        <div class="print-thumb">Custom Theme</div>
        <div class="print-thumb">Digital Gallery</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
